{
  "stem": "16930.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I-- I was-- I worked for the AG Corps, Adjutant General Corps, which was running the port of Yokohama, which were bringing-- which was adjacent to-- to Tokyo, where they took up part of the port, which supplied the Americans in Japan with food, and ammunition, and clothes, and everything what the American army needs.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There's a lot of things an army needs, eggs, you know, these powder eggs, and the milk, and Coca-Colas.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, there's lot of things, besides ammunition, that an army needs, and especially American-- a luxury army like America, you know, where they have all kinds of things and facilities.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was-- and then the section I was in, we ran what they call billets for officers and civilians.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Soldiers live in barracks, you know, but officers live in billets, you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then we had requisitioned Japanese hotels, were requisitioned by the US Army, where these people were billeted.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And some of them, they also built themselves.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know, but there were some-- so I was in charge of a couple of them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, I was in charge technically.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I know nothing about hotels, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I was a guy who hadn't even, you know, finished high school really.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You know, I did not even have my high school diploma really.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was still working on it, although I'd been a teacher, a shop teacher, in Israel, and had some education.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But technically, I hadn't even--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyway, so I got this hotel, being in charge of a couple of these hotels.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there was Japanese workers under me, managers and other workers under me, who really did the job.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they had-- in all American facilities, you have to have American staff present, in case something goes wrong.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
